// Reinforce = an activated ability that functions only while the card with
// reinforce is in a player's HAND [CR#702.77a]: "Reinforce N—[cost]" means
// "[Cost], Discard this card: Put N +1/+1 counters on target creature." The
// ability keeps existing in every other zone [CR#702.77b], but only the
// from-hand activation is representable, so `from: Hand` is the
// zone-of-function seam — the same one Cycling [CR#702.29a] uses.
//
// Two params, matching the arg shape the parser emits
// (`Reinforce(N, [cost])`):
//   - `Param(0)` = N, a `Count` (the bare numeral, e.g. `Reinforce(1, …)`),
//     threaded into the counter amount as `Count::Literal(N)`.
//   - `Param(1)` = the printed [cost], the macro's list param. Wrapping it as a
//     nested `Cost(Param(1))` splices it ahead of the fixed discard-self, and
//     `Cost`'s deserialize flattens the two into one cost list — exactly the
//     Cycling discard-this construction. The discard is of THIS card
//     (`Discard(what: This)`), not a free-choice discard.
//
// The effect is a `Targeted` ([CR#115.1,601.2c], the target declared on the
// `Targeted` wrapper — the same `Target(Exactly(1), filter)` shape Modular and
// Mentor use) over "target creature" (`Type(Creature)`), placing N +1/+1
// counters [CR#122.1a] on the announced target: `PutCounters(Target(0),
// P1P1Counter, Param(0))` — the chosen target read back via `Target(0)`, the
// counter kind a bare identifier, the amount the printed N.
(
    name: "Reinforce",
    template: "reinforce ${0}—${1}",
    kinds: [KeywordAbility],
    params: [Count, Cost],
    body: Composite(
        name: "Reinforce",
        abilities: [Activated(
            from: Hand,
            cost: [Cost(Param(1)), Do(Discard(count: 1, what: This))],
            effect: Targeted(
                targets: [Target(Exactly(1), Type(Creature))],
                effect: PutCounters(Target(0), P1P1Counter, Param(0)),
            ),
        )],
    ),
)
